text:
="preserve">Madieng Khary Dieng (21 November 1932 – 27 November 2020) was a Senegalese politician. He was a member of the Socialist Party. He was a government minister several times during Abdou Diouf's presidency. Dieng was Minister of the Interior from 1991 to 1993. He also was an Ambassador to The Gambia from 1996 to 1998
Dieng was born in Coki, Senegal. He died on 27 November 2020 in Rabat, Morocco at the age of 88.
